subfield_description: An algorithm is a procedure for solving a well defined computational problem. They are used in all aspects of computer science such as artificial intelligence, databases, graphics, networking, operating systems, security, etc.
Computer architecture is a subfield carried out mostly by Computer engineers and computer scientists since they both focus on hardware design.

Consists of advancing goals in some sciences through computing, which include sciences like biology, chemistry, forensics, sociology and many more. It can apply computer simulation, math modeling, scientific visualization, data structures and algorithms, symbolic computation, networking, database design and high performance computing.
